  src/sdk/relationship-context.ts,project,Bounded context traversal; has no missing-reference handling today
body: "Evidence (2026-07-16, v2026.7.16 on main): `pm deps pm-96h7 --format context` returns missing_count:3 with node_count:21/edge_count:12, meta shows visitedNodes:737/inspectedEdges:1223 — but no missing-reference rows anywhere in the payload; `pm deps pm-96h7 --json` (tree) returns missing_count:0 and missing:null for the same root. No CLI flag enumerates the refs (--help audited). Validate's dependency_references check is status:ok with active=0, so the 3 are almost certainly legacy-terminal ghosts encountered on closed depth-2 neighbors (pm-2ler class) — exactly why enumeration + classification matters: an agent seeing a bare count cannot tell repairable active typos from ignorable history. Sibling precedent: pm-p9sc (GH-535, CLOSED PR#545) fixed the inverse contradiction (deps under-reporting vs validate). Fix should surface bounded missing rows (declaring node, dangling target, kind, active|legacy classification) in context format and align tree-format semantics."
